January 1996 was the first month of that leap year. The month, which began on a Monday, ended on a Wednesday after 31 days.

Portal:Current events[edit]

Current events of January 1, 1996 (1996-01-01) (Monday) edit history watch
  • Fahd of Saudi Arabia temporarily gives power to Crown Prince Abdullah, his legal successor, due to ill health.[clarification needed]
Current events of January 3, 1996 (1996-01-03) (Wednesday) edit history watch
  • Motorola introduces the Motorola StarTAC Wearable Cellular Telephone, the world's smallest and lightest mobile phone to date.
Current events of January 4, 1996 (1996-01-04) (Thursday) edit history watch
  • Hosni Mubarak, the President of Egypt, appoints a new government in response to accusations of corruption in the parliamentary elections; which were held the previous year, in late-1995.[clarification needed]
Current events of January 5, 1996 (1996-01-05) (Friday) edit history watch
  • Hamas operative Yahya Ayyash is assassinated by an Israeli Shabak-planted, bomb-laden cell phone.
Current events of January 7, 1996 (1996-01-07) (Sunday) edit history watch
  • One of the worst blizzards in American history hits the eastern states, killing more than 150 people. Philadelphia receives a record 30.7 inches (78 cm) of snow, New York City's public schools close for the first time in eighteen years and the federal government in Washington, D.C. is closed for days.
Current events of January 8, 1996 (1996-01-08) (Monday) edit history watch
  • A Zairean cargo plane crashes into a crowded market in the center of the capital city, Kinshasa, killing 300 people.
Current events of January 9, 1996 (1996-01-09) (Tuesday) edit history watch
  • Serious fighting breaks out between Russian soldiers and rebel fighters in Chechnya.
Current events of January 11, 1996 (1996-01-11) (Thursday) edit history watch
  • Ryutaro Hashimoto, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party, becomes Prime Minister of Japan.
Current events of January 13, 1996 (1996-01-13) (Saturday) edit history watch
  • Italy's Prime Minister, Lamberto Dini, resigns after the failure of all-party talks to confirm him. New talks are initiated by President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro to form a new government.
Current events of January 14, 1996 (1996-01-14) (Sunday) edit history watch
  • Jorge Sampaio is elected President of Portugal.
Current events of January 16, 1996 (1996-01-16) (Tuesday) edit history watch
  • President of Sierra Leone, Valentine Strasser, is deposed by the chief of defense, Julius Maada Bio. Bio promises to restore power following elections scheduled for February.
Current events of January 17, 1996 (1996-01-17) (Wednesday) edit history watch
  • Amber Hagerman, a 9-year-old American child victim and namesake for the AMBER Alert system, is murdered in Arlington, Texas.
Current events of January 19, 1996 (1996-01-19) (Friday) edit history watch
  • The North Cape oil spill occurs as an engine fire forces the tugboat Scandia ashore on Moonstone Beach in South Kingstown, Rhode Island. The North Cape Barge is pulled along with it and leaks 820,000 gallons of home heating oil.
  • An Indonesian ferry sinks off the northern tip of Sumatra, drowning more than 100 people.
Current events of January 20, 1996 (1996-01-20) (Saturday) edit history watch
  • Yasser Arafat is re-elected as president of the Palestinian Authority.
Current events of January 21, 1996 (1996-01-21) (Sunday) edit history watch
  • France undertakes its last nuclear weapons test.
Current events of January 22, 1996 (1996-01-22) (Monday) edit history watch
  • Andreas Papandreou, Prime Minister of Greece, resigns due to health problems; a new government forms under Costas Simitis.
Current events of January 24, 1996 (1996-01-24) (Wednesday) edit history watch
  • Polish Premier Józef Oleksy resigns amid charges that he spied for Moscow. He is replaced by Włodzimierz Cimoszewicz.
Current events of January 26, 1996 (1996-01-26) (Friday) edit history watch
  • Whitewater scandal: U.S. First Lady Hillary Clinton testifies before a grand jury.
Current events of January 27, 1996 (1996-01-27) (Saturday) edit history watch
  • Colonel Ibrahim Baré Maïnassara deposes the first democratically elected President of Niger, Mahamane Ousmane, in a military coup.
Current events of January 29, 1996 (1996-01-29) (Monday) edit history watch
  • President Jacques Chirac announces a "definitive end" to French nuclear testing.
  • Fire destroys La Fenice, Venice's opera house.
Current events of January 30, 1996 (1996-01-30) (Tuesday) edit history watch
  • Irish National Liberation Army leader Gino Gallagher is killed in an internal feud.
  • Sarah Balabagan is caned in the United Arab Emirates.
Current events of January 31, 1996 (1996-01-31) (Wednesday) edit history watch
  • Colombo Central Bank bombing: an explosives-filled truck rams into the gates of the Central Bank in Colombo, Sri Lanka, killing at least 86 people and injuring 1,400.
  • An explosion in Shaoyang, China, kills 122 people and injures over 400 when 10 short tons (9.1 t) of dynamite in an illegal explosives warehouse underneath an apartment building detonate.
  • An amateur astronomer from southern Japan discovers Comet Hyakutake; it will pass very close to the Earth in March.
